DUBAI: Saudi Islamic Minister Sheikh Abdullatif Al-Asheikh and Justice Minister Walid Al-Samaani separately toured the Kingdom’s pavilion at Expo 2020 Dubai. They were briefed on the mission of the pavilion, which showcases Saudi Arabia’s aspirations for the future, its promising investment opportunities and the diversity of its culture. Al-Asheikh also visited the pavilion of the UAE, which sheds light on the history of the country and the impact of the joint work plan adopted by the Emirates to achieve growth and prosperity. He visited the pavilions of the Gulf Cooperation Council, Egypt, Indonesia and Greece. He was briefed on the collections displayed, which illustrate culture, heritage and civilizational and social diversity. The Saudi justice minister praised the Kingdom’s efforts in the event, which he said reflect the aspirations of the Saudi leadership to achieve its vision and build a bright future. The Saudi pavilion offers more than 1,800 events, activities, programs and themed weeks. There is also a sustainable energy station, a strong presence of Saudi heritage handicrafts, shows featuring popular folklore and famous cuisines from all of the Kingdom’s regions. Expo 2020 visitors can take part in discovery tours hosted by the Saudi pavilion.